## Security Relevance
- Splunk helps security teams detect suspicious activity across many data sources in one place.
- Indexted and normalized data improve investigations
- Alerts and dashboards support faster response to incidents

## SOC Analyst Perspective
- Splunk gives SOC analysts a central place to search and investigate logs
- Reports, dashboards and alerts help analysts act from the raw data
- Data models make investigations more efficient

## Key Takeaways
- Splunk is a unified data platform that makes machine data searchable, usable and valuable
- Splunk core ability is converting large amounts of system and application data into operational and security insights
- Supports detection, investigation, monitoring, and incident response in a single environment



